No form of the word [[Democracy|democracy]] is found in the Constitution. Some framers of the document argued (perhaps most notably in the [[Federalist Papers]], especially 10 and 51) that democracy in its pure form is a danger to liberty, and that the natural impulses of factions and majority should be dampened via a [[Republic|republican]] framework. Hence, for example, Senators were to be elected to 6-year terms by their respective state legislatures, and President and Vice President were to be chosen via 
